      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "There was merit in the latest performance of OUR SUNSET DELIGHT (1) when he came from the back row to be beaten just over 7 metres. Owns a decent record at this longer distance and the ace draw gives him every chance to show his best. CHARGE AHEAD (5) has struggled to find the form that saw him Group 1 placed in Sydney last season but there has been some solid recent efforts including a placing three back at this circuit and distance. He would win this with anything like his best. CLASSIE WASHINGTON NZ (7) draws wider but was solid in a resuming fifth in stronger company. Decent second-up record so should be improved. KOSIMO (6) can feature again after he raced parked from this barrier but boxed on to be beaten less than 3m into second here last week.",
